node.title: Healy blasts Australia to World Cup win
node.description: Australia have won the ICC Women's Cricket World Cup, defeating England by 71 runs in Christchurch.
node.content:
["Australia have won the ICC Women's Cricket World Cup, defeating England by 71 runs in Christchurch.", "", "
Alyssa Healy celebrates her century Photo: © Photosport Ltd 2022
", "Wicketkeeper Alyssa Healy dominated for Australia with the bat, clobbering 26 boundaries on her way to 170 from 138 balls.", "The innings is a new World Record for an ICC Final, passing fellow Australian Adam Gilchrist's 149 from the 2007 World Cup decider.", "Healy shared an opening stand of 160 with Rachel Haynes, before Beth Mooney joined in on the action with a swift 62 from 47 balls.", "The English bowlers managed to stem the run rate after the dismissal of Healy in the 46th over, but the damage had well and truly been done.", "Australia finished with 356 for 5, and England came out to bat facing a required run rate of 7.14.", "Regular wickets cost England at crucial times, as several partnerships showed potential before being undone by sharp bowling from the Australians.", "Nat Sciver was a shining light in England's valiant run chase, reaching her century from 90 balls in a fine display of shot making.", "Sciver fought to the end, including a ninth wicket partnership of 65 with Charlie Dean to give England a glimmer of hope.", "Dean was eventually caught for 21 with the score at 278, and seven runs later it was all over when Anya Shrubsole skied a ball from Jess Jonassen.", "The victory was thoroughly deserved for the Australian side who showed throughout the tournament that they were the best side, winning all nine of their matches en route to the title.", "A healthy crowd showed up to Hagley Oval to attend the match, with outdoor capacity restrictions recently being lifted.", "RNZ"]
